Description: Upper part of a curved-topped limestone stela; at the top is the prenomen of Amenemhat III flanked by Osiris and Wepwawet; below are ten(surviving) rows of Hieroglyphic text.
Curator's comments: PM VII: 406 Published: HTBM 4: Plate 14. See now A. Meza, Ancient Egypt in Malta in Egyptology at the Dawn of the 21st Century III, 307-314. See also C. Testa, in Heritage 74: an encyclopaedia of Maltese culture and civilisation, 1473-7. PM VII, p. 406
Bibliographic references: Hall 1913 / Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs, etc. in the British Museum (pl.14)
Young et al 2009 / Egyptian stelae from Malta (p.23-30, p.24, fig.1, p.26, fig.6, p.28, fig.7a)
